	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here's another idea: HSL 4.2.2<br /><br /><ul><li>When bits 7-4 are 0000, the color is grayscale and bits 3-0 are the luminance.</li><li>Otherwise, bits 7-4 specify hue (in steps of 24ยบ), bits 3-2 the saturation (25%,50%,75%,100%) and bits 1-0 the luminance (20%,40%,60%,80%).</li></ul><br />EDIT: fixed my HSL algorithm and ditched the old image<br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/gkd8tL1.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Still leaves a lot to be desired.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
